This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with argumentation mining, which is a subfield of natural language processing. The use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) also suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves sequence labeling, which is a common task in information retrieval, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of neural networks to analyze text data may also suggest that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
